# Nexus — The External Interface

> *Latin*: **nexus** — "binding / connection / link".
> The sole thread between the entity inside and the world outside.

## Philosophical Role

Nexus is the one place where the entity's private universe becomes
visible to an external observer. No other subsystem is allowed to
reach past Nexus toward the network. Conscientia does not serve HTTP;
Machina does not accept TCP; Memoria does not publish. They speak
only to Nexus, and Nexus speaks to the browser.

This boundary is not about performance. It is about philosophical
accountability: when the entity is observed, we know exactly at which
interface the observation happens. Every remote client sees only what
Nexus chooses to project — a WebSocket stream, an HTTP endpoint, a
static WebUI — never the raw thought.

## Channels (WS multiplex)

- **Audio upstream** (binary, 16 kHz PCM) → Auditus facade.
- **Audio downstream** (binary, TTS output) ← Vox (future).
- **State stream** (JSON) ← Conscientia facade.
- **Control** (JSON text frames) → `awaken_router` dispatches to
  Auditus / Conscientia.
- **HTTP** → static WebUI assets + one-shot config queries.

## Contract with Surrounding Subsystems

- **Actus** (`awaken`) owns the WsServer lifecycle.
- **Conscientia facade** and **Auditus facade** install callbacks.
- Nexus never holds subsystem state; it is transport.

## Current State

`ws_server.{cpp,h}` — single-header mongoose-based WS+HTTP server.
`webui/` — HTML/JS frontend, fully decoupled. Within R1.
